Instructions to run the MPI version of HERMES.

1. Install the conda environemnt hermes_mpi.yml in the HPC cluster (linux environment).
2. Activate: conda activate env_name
3. Load the tiff file and voxel resolution
4. Under croppingFlag == 'Regular' set the cube length and number of volumes to be generated. 

Now in the submission script, adjust the 

#!/bin/bash                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              
#SBATCH -t 0-0:29:59 # hours, min, sec
#SBATCH --job-name=NAME
#SBATCH --nodes=XXX
#SBATCH --partition=PARTITION 
#SBATCH --exclusive (optional but preferred)

#make sure conda env is active

mpirun -n YYY /home/.conda/envs/hermes_mpi/bin/python voxel2stl.py

AN EXAMPLE:
XXX - is the number of nodes available/allocated. 
YYY - Number of CPU
Example: If 2 nodes are available then XXX = 2

If each Node has 128 GB memory then 2 nodes = 128*2 GB memory allocated to code

YYY is number of CPU (make sure ample memory is there)